  "title": "Service Crew (5/6 Days Work) new join bonus!",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></u></p>\n<p>· Propertable setting including setting up items</p>\n<p>· Replenish supplies such as serviette, table ware and refill condiments</p>\n<p>· Usher customer to their table</p>\n<p>· Present menus to customers, inform customers of promotional items and answer questions about menu items, making recommendations upon request</p>\n<p>· Taking customers’ order and prepare drinks and dessert to customer</p>\n<p>· Serve food and beverages to customers</p>\n<p>· Clean tables after customers have finished dining and take them to kitchen for cleaning</p>\n<p>· Perform cashiering at times</p>\n<p>· Perform opening and closing duties</p>\n<p>· Perform other reasonable job duties as requested by Supervisors</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<p>· Minimum GCE N-Level or, ITE qualifications</p>\n<p>· Able to perform split shift and work on weekends and public holidays</p>\n<p>· With F&amp;B experience is an asset but not essential</p>\n<p>· Good communication skills and ability to communicate with customers with smile all the time</p>\n<p>· Pleasant and cheerful personality, energetic and team player</p>\n<p>· Willing to learn and has passion for service industry</p>\n<p>· Able to multi-task and adapt to fast paced environment</p>\n<p>· Possess WSQ Food &amp; Hygiene Certificate</p>\n<p>· Knowledge in POS system</p>",
